- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with analyzing popular music using algorithms and machine learning techniques.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper involves collecting and indexing data from Wikipedia.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the dataset includes features related to sociology and psychology.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses machine learning techniques to find trends and predict future music genres.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the intersection of technology and popular culture.
